Step 2 CSS (not required)


1. Add a color to your text so it looks better!
  #text-holder {
  color: blue;
}


2. Add the Width you want your text to display to have!
#text-holder {
  color: brown;
  width:50%;
}


3. Now add the Text size!
#text-holder {
  color: brown;
  width:50%;
  font-size:15px;
}


4. Now add the Font to make your text more stylish!
#text-holder {
  color: brown;
  width:50%;
  font-size:15px;
  font-family:'Courier New';
}


5. Now add the background color!
#text-holder {
  color: brown;
  width:50%;
  font-size:15px;
  font-family:'Courier New';
  background: #f9f9f9;
}
